Subject: Dictated Codex Conversation Agent Spawn Node Source

Description: Preserved source note for the node that spawns LM Studio hosted Codex CLI instances around a root submission attached to a Codex app conversation.

& [DictatedCodexConversationAgentSpawnNodeSource] is the preserved user direction
  + [source_status] is preserved_raw_direction
  + [captured_request] is that should be the node that spawns instances of Codex CLI hosted by LM Studio to coordinate agents around a job as defined by the root submission attached to a Codex app conversation
  + [root_submission_shape] is the original user or agent submission that defines the job
  + [conversation_attachment_shape] is the Codex app conversation that owns the human-facing authority and re-entry context
  + [spawn_shape] is a controlled node that launches or queues Codex CLI instances through LM Studio-hosted local inference only after gates pass
  + [coordination_shape] is worker agents orbiting the job frame and returning captured contributions into the LLM agent collaboration fabric
  + [preservation_boundary] is source direction only, not implementation authority until processed and gated
  + [outside] is automatic spawning, unbounded Codex CLI launch, hidden cost, credentials, direct file mutation, and worker authority without Codex app review

  = must: preserve root submission and Codex app conversation attachment
  = must: treat Codex CLI hosted by LM Studio as a desired node shape subject to context and launch gates
  = must: keep spawning blocked until stop, cost, capture, concurrency, context, and authority gates are visible
